  "prompt": "Why should you not flush a tampon down the toilet?",
  "response": "Flushing a tampon down the toilet is generally not recommended for several reasons:\n\n1. **Plumbing Issues**: Tampons can cause blockages in plumbing systems because they do not break down easily in water. This can lead to costly repairs for clogged pipes and damage to plumbing infrastructure.\n\n2. **Environmental Concerns**: Tampons can contribute to environmental pollution. They do not biodegrade quickly and can end up in waterways, causing harm to marine life and ecosystems.\n\n3. **Sewage System Problems**: Tampons can interfere with sewage treatment processes. They can clog pumps and screens at treatment facilities, leading to operational difficulties and increased maintenance costs.\n\n4. **Public Health Risks**: Improper disposal of tampons can lead to public health issues if they cause blockages that result in sewage backups and leaks.\n\nTo prevent these issues, it is better to dispose of tampons in a trash bin. Many public restrooms provide special bins for sanitary products.",
